# issue: https://github.com/vectordotdev/vrl/issues/453
#
# Regression test: a discarded fallible expression earlier in a block
# (here `set(...)` on line 4) used to be incorrectly attributed to the
# next assignment (line 5) as a confusing "unhandled fallible
# assignment" error. The error must now be reported on the actual
# fallible expression as `unhandled error`.
#
# result:
#
# error[E100]: unhandled error
#   ┌─ :4:5
#   │
# 4 │     set(e, [key], value)
#   │     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
#   │     │
#   │     expression can result in runtime error
#   │     handle the error case to ensure runtime success
#   │
#   = see documentation about error handling at https://errors.vrl.dev/#handling
#   = learn more about error code 100 at https://errors.vrl.dev/100
#   = see language documentation at https://vrl.dev
#   = try your code in the VRL REPL, learn more at https://vrl.dev/examples
output = []
for_each(.) -> |key, value| {
    e = {}
    set(e, [key], value)
    output = push(output, e)
}
. = output
